    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="964"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 133.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy and
                    translation of the law<note n="1" xml:id="d964fn1">Not printed.</note> enacted
                    by the National Constituent Assembly electing Gen. Luis Mena as President for
                    the constitutional term beginning January 1, 1913, and ending January 31, 1916,
                    and Col. Fernando Solorzano as Vice President for the same period. This law was
                    approved in second debate by a vote of 29 to 2.</p>
                <p>This double elections has been well received. Since it occurred conditions have
                    had a more settled and peaceful appearance than in sometime.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. M. Gunther.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
